    {
      "id": "upload.create-session",
      "rest": ["POST /api/uploads"],
      "graphql": { "status": "stable", "field": "createUploadSession" },
      "mcp": {
        "status": "registered_operation",
        "tools": ["run_graphql_operation"]
      },
      "semantics": "multi_step_storage_workflow",
      "notes": [
        "GraphQL and MCP may reserve quota and return the authenticated on-site PUT workflow URL; raw object bytes remain exclusive to the R2-backed HTTP route.",
        "MCP-resource bearer tokens are not replayable at the REST upload URL; clients need a browser session or a separately authorized REST upload token for the byte-transfer step.",
        "The registered operation is marked destructive because its bounded oldest-first stale-session sweep may delete expired R2 objects after confirming storage cleanup."
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "upload.complete",
      "rest": ["POST /api/uploads/complete"],
      "graphql": { "status": "stable", "field": "completeUploadSession" },
      "mcp": {
        "status": "registered_operation",
        "tools": ["run_graphql_operation"]
      },
      "semantics": "multi_step_storage_workflow",
      "notes": [
        "Completion validates the existing R2 object and commits metadata; GraphQL and MCP never receive or proxy object bytes.",
        "Expiry or quota cleanup deletes or confirms the pending R2 object is absent before removing UploadPending. Quota failure first expires the row in the serializable transaction to prevent concurrent completion; storage failure returns GraphQL SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE and preserves the pending row for retry."
      ]
    },
    {
